   <h1>Semester Program</h1>

</p>
<p>For those students seeking a shorter term program, ISE is happy to provide a semester abroad in a foreign country. A student will still be able to enjoy an outbound semester program without sacrificing the same benefits of a full year program. By immersing oneself into another culture, a student will gain a new perspective on life while learning a new language, meeting new people, and appreciating the importance of multicultural diversity. </p>

<p><strong>Program Info:</strong> The price of ISE's Outbound programs includes health insurance, homestay room and board, and school(except where additional school fees are noted). The cost of the program does not include round trip ticket and spending cash per month for each student. ISE requires each student to arrive with $300 spending cash for each month of a student's program. </p>


<p><strong>Payment Policy:</strong><br />
